Detailed Description

Class used for map generation specific tasks not needed by the mc2 server.

Use MC2MapGenUtil if the server needs access.

mapSupAndVerPair MapGenUtil::getMapSupAndVer (  const char *  gdfMapOrigin  )  [static]
 

Parameters:
gdfMapOrigin String containing both map supplier and map version. The map supplier is separated from the map version by the first '_'.
Returns:
Returns map supplier and map version from a map origin string. If map supplier can't be defined, MapGenEnums::unknownSupplier is returned. If map origin can't be defined, MapGenEnums::invMapVersion is returned.

bool MapGenUtil::loadTxtFileTable (  MC2String  fileName,
uint32  nbrCols,
MC2String  colSeparator,
vector< vector< MC2String > > &  tableContent,
uint32  skipStartRows = 0,
uint32  skipEndRows = 0,
map< MC2String, uint32 > *  prefixNbrCols = NULL,
set< uint32 > *  throwAwayCols = NULL
)  [static]
 

Reads the content of a text file with text data in columns and rows.

Puts each cell in a MC2String organized in nested vectors.

Parameters:
fileName Name and path to the file to load.
nbrCols Number of columns in the file. Used for sanity check.
colSeparator The sign or signs used for separating colunn values.
tableContent Outparameter. The result is put here. One vector per row containing a vector with a MC2String per colunn of that row.
skipStartRows Read past skipStartRows rows at the beginning of the file.
skipEndRows Don't read endStartRows rows at the end of the file.
prefixNbrCols Use this parameter when number of columns of rows differ depending on the value of column 0. Key: Colunn 0 (prefix) value Value: Expected number of columns for this prefix.
throwAwayCols To save memory, throw away not needed values right away.
Returns:
True if successful, otherwise false.

bool MapGenUtil::saveTxtFileTable (  MC2String  fileName,
uint32  nbrCols,
MC2String  colSeparator,
vector< vector< MC2String > > &  tableContent
)  [static]
 

Writes teh contenet of table of text to a separated row based file.

Parameters:
fileName Name and path to the file to save.
nbrCols Number of columns in the file. Used for sanity check.
colSeparator The sign or signs used for separating colunn values.
tableContent This is the data to be written to the file. Each outer vector element is a vector representing row and each element in the row vectors is representing a columnvalue of that row.
Returns:
True if successful, otherwise false.
